org.tiledreader

Class TiledMap

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.tiledreader.TiledResource
      • org.tiledreader.TiledMap

  • public class TiledMap
extends TiledResource

    A TiledMap represents an entire map made with Tiled. It corresponds to a <map> tag in a Tiled XML file.

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      static class  TiledMap.Orientation
      Represents an orientation that a Tiled map can have.
      static class  TiledMap.RenderOrder
      Represents an order in which the tiles in a Tiled map's tile layers can be rendered.
      static class  TiledMap.StaggerAxis
      Represents an axis that can be staggered in a Tiled map with a staggered or hexagonal orientation.
      static class  TiledMap.StaggerIndex
      Represents a category of indices that can be shifted in a Tiled map with a staggered or hexagonal orientation.

      • getTopLevelLayers

        public final java.util.List<TiledLayer> getTopLevelLayers()
        Returns an unmodifiable List view of all of this map's layers that are not descendants of group layers, sorted from back to front in terms of rendering order. To explore the hierarchy of all of this map's layers, you can iterate through this list and, whenever you encounter a group layer, recursively explore the list of its child layers.
        Returns:
        This map's top-level layers

      • getNonGroupLayers

        public final java.util.List<TiledLayer> getNonGroupLayers()
        Returns an unmodifiable List view of all of this map's layers that are not group layers, sorted from back to front in terms of rendering order. These layers are the ones that contain actual content, as group layers are just an organizational tool.
        Returns:
        This map's non-group layers

      • getProperties

        public final java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> getProperties()
        Returns an unmodifiable Map view of this map's custom properties. Each key in the Map is the name of a property, and its corresponding value is the value of that property. The type of the value object corresponds to the type of the property: String for a string property, Integer for an int, Float for a float, Boolean for a bool, java.awt.Color for a color, and java.io.File for a file.
        Returns:
        This map's custom properties

      • getProperty

        public final java.lang.Object getProperty(java.lang.String name)

The type of the returned value corresponds to the type of the property: String for a string property, Integer for an int, Float for a float, Boolean for a bool, java.awt.Color for a color, and java.io.File for a file.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the property whose value is to be returned
